    Aust N Z J Surg. 1994 Jun;64(6):387-8.

The results of external beam radiotherapy for clinically localized 
adenocarcinoma of the prostate in 448 patients treated in the period 1980-90 
were reviewed. The average follow up was 4.9 years. The patients were aged 44-87 
