DESIGN: Retrospective study.
SETTING: Department of surgery, University Medical Centre, Amsterdam, the 
Netherlands.
METHODS: Retrospective review of the records of 32 HIV seropositive patients 
surgically treated for anorectal pathology in 1985-1992.
RESULTS: The 32 patients, homosexual males, had a total of 46 diagnoses for 
