primarily with a malignancy (3 with squamous cell carcinoma of the anus, 1 with 
cloacogenic carcinoma, 1 with non-Hodgkin lymphoma distally in the rectum). 
Twelve patients died within 6 months after the first operation.
CONCLUSION: In choosing therapy for anorectal disorders, the limited survival of 
HIV seropositive patients, especially those with an advanced stage of AIDS 
should be considered. Surgical treatment can improve the quality of life in 
these patients.

